data.description: The home you have been waiting for! You will love this stunning home that features abundant mature trees and is in the Trophy Oaks subdivision 5 miles south of Somerset and 25 miles south of downtown San Antonio. Backing up to a large ranch, this French country home was built in 2007, designed by Architect Brian Smith and everything about it is customized. It is four sides masonry with massive rock columns in the front and back. It has a beautiful blue standing seam metal roof that changes hues depending on the angle of the sun. Step inside the front door under the covered porch to a substantial great room with vaulted ceiling. The floor to ceiling wood burning fireplace is also constructed out of the white limestone rock.  Adjacent to the great room is the perfectly appointed kitchen with custom knotty alder cabinets. Features in the kitchen include granite countertops, two sinks  one being for kitchen prep- double ovens, propane gas stove, dishwasher, under cabinet lights, island, and breakfast bar. The living/breakfast areas open onto the spacious back porch and back yard. A massive Live Oak, estimated to be over 400 years old, provides shade for the back round patio and grilling station. The master bedroom and bedroom #2 are split from the 2 bedrooms in the other side of the home. Bedroom #2 is currently used for a home office, but could easily flex into a nursery, home gym or separate media room. The other two bedrooms are separated by a jack n jill bathroom, though each bedroom has its own vanity separated from the rooms by pocket doors. Every bedroom has a walk-in closet, and the master bath has two along with double vanities, a whirlpool tub and walk-in fully tiled shower. The half bath is conveniently located near the kitchen and has a door to access the back porch in the event new owners want to install a pool and have easy bath access. The laundry room, near the kitchen and garage access, has built in cabinets and room for an extra refrigerator.  The home has a 3-car garage and attic access is in the garage with STAIRS to the decked attic area, no more climbing drop-down stairs for storage! There is a pole barn on the property for storage of farm implements. There is also a stall and other run in in the back pasture.  The property is fenced and cross-fenced. The front has a wrought iron fence with a solar automatic double gate.  The landscaping is delightful. The current owner has planted over 25 crepe myrtles along with other shrubs and flowers.  The outdoor area is graced by small stone walls and planters. Live oaks, hickory and burr oaks are abundant on this 10.274-acre property. A timed sprinkler system provides ease of watering for the avid gardener. There is a buried 500-gallon propane tank that fuels the cooking: 2 on demand water heaters, the furnace and gas dryer. The home is extremely energy efficient utilizing a single Carrier AC unit with 3 separate zones.  There is a water softener in a dedicated garage closet and a 220V electrical box is available for future use.    Sellers are licensed real estate brokers/agents. A short leaseback is preferable.
